-- Crystal Palace Manager Ian Holloway Leaves Club, Sky Reports
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-10-23T15:42:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-23/crystal-palace-manager-ian-holloway-leaves-club-sky-reports.html
Crystal Palace manager  Ian Holloway 
has left the club, which is one place off the bottom of English
soccer’s Premier League,  Sky Sports  reported citing unidentified
sources.  Palace has three points from eight games, two ahead of
Sunderland. The southeast London club lost 4-1 at home to Fulham
two days ago.  Holloway took Palace into the Premier League with victory
in last season’s Championship playoffs. He’s managed clubs
including Bristol Rovers, Queens Park Rangers and Blackpool.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christopher Elser in London at 
